## B.8 LOTO Notice

> **LOCKOUT/TAGOUT — DISCLOSURE COMPLIANCE:**  
>  
> Any DNAI-compliant system operating in a consequential domain (housing, employment, healthcare, credit, criminal justice, public services) must treat the following as physically blocked unless disclosure requirements are met:  
>  
> - Delivery of consequential decisions without plain-language explanation  
> - Collection of feedback data without disclosure and opt-out mechanism  
> - Operation in a jurisdiction where the system cannot meet Level 1 Disclosure requirements  
> - Deployment of model updates without re-running Seaworthiness Assessment  
>  
> **Status: LOCKED.** Disclosure gates are not policy options — they are seaworthiness requirements. A system that cannot disclose its patterns to the people it affects is not fit for deployment.

